      "message": "Soon, I\u0027m going to rip the constness off the code so we don\u0027t have the dumb const_casts. I don\u0027t want to do the setAdvance* because I hope to make almost all the fields const. The ultimate goal is SkGlyph(id, advanceX, advanceY, width, height, top, left, format). Those should fields all be const.\n\nMainly, I want to work on the client side, and save the scaler side for later. The client code doesn\u0027t seem to get all the invariants right at call sites. Now fAdvance* is not really a problem, but fPathData, and fImage are. Basically clients abuse the openness of SkGlyph while the Scalers seem to be more careful.",
